<node id="GraphRAG">
  <data key="d0">GraphRAG</data>
  <data key="d1">organization</data>
  <data key="d2">GraphRAG is a method that represents a shift in retrieval-augmented generation, enhancing traditional systems by incorporating knowledge graphs.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG refers to architectures that combine graph-based retrieval and generation methods in AI applications.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG is a method for addressing LLM hallucination by grounding generation in structured knowledge graphs to enhance accuracy.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG is a system that utilizes community detection to enhance its global search capability within knowledge graphs.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG is a retrieval-augmented generation system known for its traceability through knowledge graph citation chains and is impacted by the EU AI Act's requirements.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG is an entity that excels at multi-hop reasoning across multiple data dimensions in the context of clinical trials.&lt;SEP&gt;GraphRAG systems utilize knowledge graph grounding to create structured domain knowledge representations that support verification.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5a0ea94d36e16aefbbdb1e52a48a4da2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ebd7175a1f26b79908061ab57b517a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-05b5cd1a96253bf7b78dbf8d300adadd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d384bfeec843c653b989ee99228eeab0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-bf191c61f24f06aa1b4b87fbbe8f257b&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-374ba872e4abd46815b626ad73ecb0b9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f13ffed8f2c81a7ff9b29900ecd42a3e</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774993823</data>
  <data key="d6"></data>
</node>
<node id="Leiden Community Detection Method">
  <data key="d0">Leiden Community Detection Method</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">The Leiden Community Detection Method is an algorithm used to identify and organize entities into hierarchical communities within a graph.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-5a0ea94d36e16aefbbdb1e52a48a4da2</data>
  <data key="d4">unknown_source</data>
  <data key="d5">1774993492</data>
