<node id="Retrieval-Augmented Generation">
  <data key="d0">Retrieval-Augmented Generation</data>
  <data key="d1">method</data>
  <data key="d2">Retrieval-Augmented Generation is a method that enhances AI systems by allowing them to answer complex queries based on traversing knowledge graphs rather than simple pattern matching.&lt;SEP&gt;Retrieval-Augmented Generation is a method that enhances the capabilities of standard AI applications by integrating retrieval and generation processes.&lt;SEP&gt;Retrieval-Augmented Generation (RAG) refers to the method where retrieval techniques enhance the generation process, particularly in AI systems.&lt;SEP&gt;Retrieval-augmented generation is a basic grounding approach that enhances model prompts with relevant documents for contextual grounding.</data>
  <data key="d3">chunk-6f15d160ead15b98ce0ab2ffb63b362a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-7ebd7175a1f26b79908061ab57b517a0&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-884ce470afe0321907650814428fae37&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f13ffed8f2c81a7ff9b29900ecd42a3e</data>
